    • 方法详细资料

      • onScreenDim

        public abstract void onScreenDim()
        Used to detect when the watch is dimming.
        Remember to make gray-scale versions of your watch face so they won't burn and drain battery unnecessarily.

      • onScreenAwake

        public abstract void onScreenAwake()
        Used to detect when the watch is not in a dimmed state.
        This does not handle when returning "home" from a different activity/application.

      • onWatchFaceRemoved

        public void onWatchFaceRemoved()
        Used to detect when a watch face is being removed (switched).
        You can either do what you need here, or simply override onDestroy().

      • onScreenOff

        public void onScreenOff()
        When the screen is OFF due to "Always-On" being disabled.
